my_data %>% 
  inner_join(code_names, by = "code") %>% 
  inner_join(st_pop_2019, by = "name") %>%
  filter(lubridate::month(as_of) == 6) %>% 
  mutate(week_num = lubridate::week(as_of)) %>% 
  group_by(code) %>%
  summarize(case_growth = (max(cases) - min(cases)) / min(cases),
            test_growth = (max(tests) - min(tests)) / min(tests)) %>% 
  
  ggplot(mapping = aes(x = case_growth, y = test_growth)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_smooth(method = "lm", linetype = 2, alpha = 0)
## `geom_smooth()` using formula 'y ~ x'

done
